1
00:02:39,280 --> 00:02:41,960
{\an8}Finish this drink first, then you can go.

2
00:02:48,800 --> 00:02:49,960
{\an8}You're getting close to the target.

3
00:02:51,840 --> 00:02:53,040
{\an8}You don't believe

4
00:02:53,120 --> 00:02:55,800
{\an8}that Lirin, the inspector's youngest,
is dead, do you?

5
00:03:04,240 --> 00:03:07,000
Taiga, did you see the board this morning?

6
00:03:07,080 --> 00:03:10,120
Stocks and 3C-Coin got smashed.

7
00:03:11,120 --> 00:03:12,760
Do you know who did it?

8
00:03:16,760 --> 00:03:18,080
Ratee's father.

9
00:03:24,600 --> 00:03:25,640
You know,

10
00:03:27,240 --> 00:03:29,200
if Taiga just says the word,

11
00:03:30,240 --> 00:03:32,880
I can even buy this entire building.

12
00:03:40,720 --> 00:03:44,880
I bet Mr. Taiga doesn't know
this is what you think.

13
00:03:45,680 --> 00:03:48,440
It's true that
I haven't known him for long,

14
00:03:48,520 --> 00:03:53,280
but you can't understand
the heart of an artist as well as I do.

15
00:04:03,760 --> 00:04:05,280
Then just you wait.

16
00:04:06,160 --> 00:04:11,520
Very soon, I'll take over Cosmic Central
as my wedding gift to him.

17
00:04:14,520 --> 00:04:15,800
No way!

18
00:04:17,240 --> 00:04:18,560
Yeah?

19
00:04:19,880 --> 00:04:23,840
What could someone like you
possibly maintain?

20
00:04:24,600 --> 00:04:28,280
You keep walking tall,
but your role is meaningless.

21
00:04:29,400 --> 00:04:32,840
You contribute nothing
to the company's profit.

22
00:04:36,240 --> 00:04:39,200
You're an outsider.
Don't act like you know everything.

23
00:04:41,960 --> 00:04:43,880
I've done my research.

24
00:04:44,920 --> 00:04:48,160
If I'm going to put my dog on a leash,

25
00:04:49,160 --> 00:04:53,120
I'll make sure its leash and collar
are pretty and perfect for it.

26
00:04:57,040 --> 00:05:02,560
Don't worry, I've chosen a collar
that's perfect for Cosmic Central Group.

27
00:05:03,320 --> 00:05:04,320
You won't be embarrassed.

28
00:05:46,360 --> 00:05:48,040
Hey, man. I need your help.

29
00:05:48,720 --> 00:05:51,880
I want to know about the company
who tanked 3C-Coin.

30
00:05:54,440 --> 00:05:58,240
I'm going to deal with them, of course.
But not to their faces.

31
00:06:13,440 --> 00:06:14,560
You can let me go now.

32
00:06:19,320 --> 00:06:20,400
Wait.

33
00:06:23,320 --> 00:06:25,320
Move a muscle, and I'll do it for real.

34
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:27,800
You sure are worth what you're paid.

35
00:06:27,880 --> 00:06:31,240
I don't work for you. Stay away from me.

36
00:06:50,800 --> 00:06:51,840
Hey!

37
00:07:01,800 --> 00:07:03,240
Madam,

38
00:07:04,440 --> 00:07:09,200
you're using your dad's company
to attack 3C-Coin and 3C Group.

39
00:07:10,720 --> 00:07:12,560
Taiga's got nothing to do with this.

40
00:07:12,640 --> 00:07:14,560
This one was all you, madam.

41
00:07:15,920 --> 00:07:19,200
Love and jealousy sure beat all.

42
00:07:20,040 --> 00:07:20,880
Cornball.

43
00:07:21,840 --> 00:07:24,320
So it's true. I was spot on, right?

44
00:07:24,400 --> 00:07:26,080
You could tell it was me?

45
00:07:27,200 --> 00:07:28,360
Who am I?

46
00:07:30,960 --> 00:07:32,720
I'm an unemployed drifter.

47
00:07:32,800 --> 00:07:35,960
I day trade just to get by
and be able to afford coffee.

48
00:07:36,040 --> 00:07:38,160
Taiga should really choose his friends.

49
00:07:38,760 --> 00:07:40,120
He did.

50
00:07:40,200 --> 00:07:43,040
He chooses based on looks.

51
00:07:48,040 --> 00:07:49,000
So,

52
00:07:49,680 --> 00:07:51,680
what do I get from talking to you?

53
00:07:51,760 --> 00:07:53,840
Nothing! What a waste of time.

54
00:07:59,360 --> 00:08:00,400
Just listen for once.

55
00:08:01,040 --> 00:08:05,280
What I'm trying to say
is even I could find out it was you

56
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:07,600
who intentionally tanked 3C,

57
00:08:07,680 --> 00:08:10,840
so, of course, the experts
could find that out too.

58
00:08:10,920 --> 00:08:13,200
But isn't it normal?
It's just a part of investment.

59
00:08:14,760 --> 00:08:18,240
Are you sure about making 3C your enemy?

60
00:08:23,880 --> 00:08:26,160
Just worry about
your own future, you giant bear.

61
00:08:26,240 --> 00:08:28,440
If I didn't ask, stay out of it.

62
00:08:32,919 --> 00:08:34,400
What a cute nickname.

63
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:36,799
"You giant bear."

64
00:08:36,880 --> 00:08:41,000
Well, suit yourself then,
Madam Problematic.

65
00:08:49,240 --> 00:08:52,960
Put away her stuff
and get her something to drink.

66
00:08:53,040 --> 00:08:54,040
Understood.

67
00:08:57,560 --> 00:08:58,560
Go get some rest.

68
00:08:59,320 --> 00:09:00,280
Yes, sir.

69
00:09:07,400 --> 00:09:09,440
You're Naruban's driver?

70
00:09:10,120 --> 00:09:11,200
Yes, ma'am.

71
00:09:12,560 --> 00:09:16,360
How strange. He's never hired
a female driver before.

72
00:09:17,800 --> 00:09:21,360
I used to work at the office.
I was also a security guard.

73
00:09:22,120 --> 00:09:26,280
Really? A pretty face like you
as security?

74
00:09:28,360 --> 00:09:32,480
You look like you're around Nun's age.

75
00:09:37,960 --> 00:09:41,000
Oh, Rin. What are you doing here?

76
00:09:41,080 --> 00:09:42,560
I'm Mr. Naruban's driver.

77
00:09:50,240 --> 00:09:51,480
You can go get some rest.

78
00:09:51,560 --> 00:09:52,520
Understood.

79
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:02,400
I beg you, Techut. She works for your dad.

80
00:10:04,600 --> 00:10:07,520
Don't worry, Mom.
I know a snack when I see one.

81
00:10:35,480 --> 00:10:36,840
Have a seat, Mr. Taiga.

82
00:10:56,040 --> 00:10:59,840
If Cosmic Central
would invest in fashion products,

83
00:10:59,920 --> 00:11:02,880
would the Kenji brand
be interested in partnering with us?

84
00:11:05,240 --> 00:11:06,840
I appreciate the offer,

85
00:11:06,920 --> 00:11:09,800
but we like to keep it simple
and only work with familiar faces.

86
00:11:11,600 --> 00:11:13,400
He turned us down, Nun.

87
00:11:17,880 --> 00:11:19,160
May I use your restroom?

88
00:11:19,760 --> 00:11:20,720
Of course.

89
00:11:23,920 --> 00:11:27,520
Come on. Come here. Up, up.

90
00:11:30,680 --> 00:11:31,840
Eat.

91
00:11:35,840 --> 00:11:36,960
Eat it. Aren't you hungry?

92
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:40,080
Eat it. Come on. Here.

93
00:11:42,560 --> 00:11:46,040
Meow, meow, meow.

94
00:11:46,640 --> 00:11:48,240
Eat your food, kitty.

95
00:11:48,320 --> 00:11:50,320
Eat and then sleep,

96
00:11:50,400 --> 00:11:52,280
so you won't roam around
flirting with guys.

97
00:11:52,360 --> 00:11:54,320
- Hey.
- Okay? You're so cute.

98
00:11:54,400 --> 00:11:55,280
- Hey!
- Ow!

99
00:11:56,760 --> 00:11:57,720
Madam!

100
00:11:57,800 --> 00:12:00,560
You're always hurting me and violating me.

101
00:12:05,120 --> 00:12:08,360
Hey, let me tell you something.

102
00:12:08,440 --> 00:12:12,440
Your love and jealousy for him
are like bag holding.

103
00:12:13,080 --> 00:12:14,880
You don't want to regret a loss,

104
00:12:14,960 --> 00:12:18,280
but you also don't know how long
you'll have to wait to make a profit.

105
00:12:18,360 --> 00:12:20,160
If you just sell it

106
00:12:20,240 --> 00:12:22,360
and invest in a different crypto,

107
00:12:22,440 --> 00:12:25,680
I assure you it'll be way more exciting.

108
00:12:27,320 --> 00:12:30,560
Why don't you try a new crypto like me?

109
00:12:30,640 --> 00:12:31,520
Wanna try?

110
00:12:32,480 --> 00:12:36,960
I wouldn't choose you
even if you were on discount.

111
00:12:38,800 --> 00:12:40,400
When will Taiga be back?

112
00:12:40,480 --> 00:12:41,480
I didn't ask him.

113
00:12:41,560 --> 00:12:42,520
Where'd he go?

114
00:12:42,600 --> 00:12:44,600
I'm not his wife. I didn't question him.

115
00:12:44,680 --> 00:12:45,960
- You!
- Hey!

116
00:12:46,680 --> 00:12:47,520
There you go again.

117
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:49,880
- Begging for more?
- Again and again, always hitting me.

118
00:12:49,960 --> 00:12:52,480
You silly bear. Why didn't you ask him?

119
00:12:53,280 --> 00:12:54,720
Don't you have a phone, madam?

120
00:12:56,640 --> 00:12:58,000
He turned off his phone.

121
00:13:01,440 --> 00:13:05,000
Taiga turned off his phone
to ignore Madam Problematic.

122
00:13:05,080 --> 00:13:07,480
For sure, 100%.

123
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:09,720
Oh my gosh.

124
00:13:10,920 --> 00:13:12,160
Hey, you!

125
00:13:14,040 --> 00:13:15,080
Madam!

126
00:13:15,920 --> 00:13:18,680
Enough, enough! Man!

127
00:13:18,760 --> 00:13:20,080
Watch your mouth!

128
00:13:44,400 --> 00:13:46,680
The restroom's this way, Mr. Taiga.

129
00:14:12,040 --> 00:14:13,160
Why are you scared of me?

130
00:14:14,680 --> 00:14:17,120
There's a fine line
between "scared" and "hate".

131
00:14:19,560 --> 00:14:20,680
Sorry,

132
00:14:21,280 --> 00:14:24,720
I don't quite understand Thai.

133
00:14:25,800 --> 00:14:28,480
You should learn the insults
before the compliments.

134
00:14:28,560 --> 00:14:30,200
Then, I should let you teach me.

135
00:14:34,360 --> 00:14:36,560
Do I look like a thief to you?

136
00:14:36,640 --> 00:14:40,560
This is not your home.
Even if you're a guest, have some manners.

137
00:14:41,240 --> 00:14:43,880
I bet a host like Mrs. Giranun
is well-mannered enough

138
00:14:43,960 --> 00:14:46,960
not to tell her bodyguard
to follow my every step

139
00:14:47,040 --> 00:14:49,400
and stare me down like this.

140
00:14:49,480 --> 00:14:51,640
I'm just doing my job.

141
00:14:52,360 --> 00:14:54,440
Treating a guest this way is your job?

142
00:14:55,160 --> 00:14:59,640
My job is to check up on everyone
who acts suspicious.

143
00:14:59,720 --> 00:15:02,440
You know, I'm starting to wonder.

144
00:15:04,160 --> 00:15:06,200
Since when did you start monitoring me…

145
00:15:15,640 --> 00:15:17,400
and knowing me so well?

146
00:15:53,320 --> 00:15:56,560
Hey. Look a little lively, won't you?

147
00:15:56,640 --> 00:15:58,800
I asked my dad to bring you along.

148
00:16:00,640 --> 00:16:02,280
I'm here to drive you, aren't I?

149
00:16:03,320 --> 00:16:04,800
You aren't driving now, are you?

150
00:16:13,440 --> 00:16:15,000
Has anyone ever told you

151
00:16:15,680 --> 00:16:17,080
you're not meant for fighting?

152
00:16:19,240 --> 00:16:22,000
With a pretty face and body like yours,

153
00:16:23,200 --> 00:16:26,400
you should be doing something
nice and fun.

154
00:16:37,440 --> 00:16:38,400
Nun!

155
00:16:53,200 --> 00:16:54,320
Nun is the type of girl

156
00:16:55,360 --> 00:16:57,280
who always gets what she wants.

157
00:17:08,680 --> 00:17:11,680
Mr. Taiga, listen to this seashell.

158
00:17:12,280 --> 00:17:13,480
Come on, Mr. Taiga.

159
00:17:21,560 --> 00:17:22,839
There's a sound!

160
00:17:24,960 --> 00:17:26,240
How funny.

161
00:17:26,920 --> 00:17:29,280
Listen.

162
00:18:07,400 --> 00:18:09,000
How is it? Is it good?

163
00:19:10,280 --> 00:19:11,360
Are you sick?

164
00:19:13,480 --> 00:19:15,640
Let me give you a pelvic exam.

165
00:20:04,040 --> 00:20:07,240
Get rid of Rin,
then I'll do whatever you ask.

166
00:20:48,280 --> 00:20:49,360
Don't struggle.

167
00:20:50,040 --> 00:20:51,600
Please me.

168
00:20:52,720 --> 00:20:54,640
I'll give you a promotion.

169
00:20:55,880 --> 00:20:58,240
I'll promote you faster
than my dad ever did.

170
00:20:59,400 --> 00:21:00,400
Got it?

171
00:22:14,280 --> 00:22:15,280
Okay.

172
00:22:19,320 --> 00:22:20,560
Ms. Nun,

173
00:22:20,640 --> 00:22:22,520
my online team wants to talk.

174
00:22:22,600 --> 00:22:24,240
There's an issue with our prototype.

175
00:22:26,800 --> 00:22:29,680
Sure, I'll be waiting here.

176
00:22:30,680 --> 00:22:31,560
Thank you.

177
00:22:54,320 --> 00:22:57,640
Tell the designer I want the outfit's
details to look more realistic.

178
00:23:38,040 --> 00:23:38,920
Hey!

179
00:23:57,560 --> 00:23:58,480
Techut!

180
00:24:06,760 --> 00:24:07,600
Damn it, Techut.

181
00:24:15,760 --> 00:24:18,040
Damn it, Techut!

182
00:26:46,200 --> 00:26:48,960
Get changed. Don't go anywhere.

183
00:26:50,040 --> 00:26:51,000
Do you understand, Rin?

184
00:28:14,120 --> 00:28:15,880
What do you want me to do with Techut?

185
00:28:20,840 --> 00:28:24,080
He'll never admit to it
unless there's proof.

186
00:28:25,400 --> 00:28:27,360
Your body is proof.

187
00:28:31,600 --> 00:28:32,800
I don't want to lose my job.

188
00:28:32,880 --> 00:28:34,120
I can hire you.

189
00:28:35,320 --> 00:28:37,880
Don't put up with harassment.

190
00:28:44,720 --> 00:28:49,000
Thank you, but let me make
my own decision on this.

191
00:29:32,520 --> 00:29:35,760
I handed her to you on a silver platter,
yet you let her get away.

192
00:29:37,320 --> 00:29:38,480
You suck.

193
00:29:41,640 --> 00:29:43,760
I'll make her mine today, no matter what.

194
00:29:45,880 --> 00:29:46,680
Where are you going?

195
00:29:47,760 --> 00:29:51,040
Rin already checked out last night.
Dumbass.

196
00:30:38,200 --> 00:30:39,320
Mr. Taiga!

197
00:30:42,560 --> 00:30:44,560
Why'd you come without inviting me?

198
00:30:48,000 --> 00:30:50,800
I'm ready. Should we practice surfing now?

199
00:30:51,400 --> 00:30:54,440
Ms. Nun, I have to go back to Bangkok.

200
00:30:55,680 --> 00:30:57,880
But you said you'd be free.

201
00:30:58,800 --> 00:31:01,440
I have to edit the design
with our pattern designer right away.

202
00:31:02,200 --> 00:31:03,080
I'm sorry, Ms. Nun.

203
00:31:43,120 --> 00:31:45,080
Someone came to Inspector Phumin's house.

204
00:31:46,560 --> 00:31:47,600
Yeah.

205
00:32:53,800 --> 00:32:54,840
Mom's birthday.

206
00:33:17,200 --> 00:33:20,520
{\an8}YOUNG EXECUTIVES CO-FOUND CCC
COSMIC CENTRAL CORPORATION

207
00:33:35,760 --> 00:33:37,880
Someone took the box
with the files on your family's case

208
00:33:37,960 --> 00:33:39,840
I almost had them.

209
00:33:42,200 --> 00:33:45,960
But luckily, you can still go
in and out of Naruban's house freely.

210
00:33:46,040 --> 00:33:50,560
Naruban doesn't trust me.
Rin's always monitoring me.

211
00:33:53,160 --> 00:33:56,160
I trust that you can do this.

212
00:34:05,960 --> 00:34:08,480
Who would also want
the Fire Phoenix case files?

213
00:34:34,080 --> 00:34:35,320
<i>But my dad's dead.</i>

214
00:34:36,360 --> 00:34:38,560
He spent his life working for others.

215
00:34:38,639 --> 00:34:40,360
But the law can't protect
every good person.

216
00:34:40,960 --> 00:34:41,840
Fire Phoenix

217
00:34:41,920 --> 00:34:44,199
is a secret organization that works

218
00:34:44,280 --> 00:34:46,120
to eliminate injustice in society.

219
00:34:46,199 --> 00:34:49,880
That means Fire Phoenix
can find who killed my father.

220
00:34:49,960 --> 00:34:52,679
Uncle, where is Fire Phoenix?

221
00:35:08,000 --> 00:35:09,120
{\an8}POL.LT.COL. PHUMIN PHONGRIT

222
00:35:09,200 --> 00:35:10,400
{\an8}BORN: NOVEMBER 11, 1972
DIED: NOVEMBER 1, 2018

223
00:35:20,240 --> 00:35:21,560
Inspector Phumin?

224
00:35:23,920 --> 00:35:25,920
Rin knows him too?

225
00:36:38,480 --> 00:36:41,240
{\an8}SLOW DOWN

226
00:36:44,040 --> 00:36:45,400
Get in!

227
00:36:52,280 --> 00:36:53,200
Quick!

228
00:38:19,440 --> 00:38:20,920
Your fever's gone down.

229
00:39:08,680 --> 00:39:10,000
Where are you, Rin?

230
00:40:07,120 --> 00:40:08,640
I'm sure you don't want the cops to know.

231
00:40:09,680 --> 00:40:11,000
That's why I brought you here.

232
00:40:12,840 --> 00:40:14,000
Does your wound hurt?

233
00:40:19,680 --> 00:40:20,640
I'm okay.

234
00:40:21,440 --> 00:40:22,880
You still look pale, though.

235
00:40:24,720 --> 00:40:25,720
You need to rest.

236
00:41:54,360 --> 00:41:55,400
Eat up.

237
00:42:19,640 --> 00:42:22,000
The bodyguard Dad hired called in sick.

238
00:42:22,640 --> 00:42:24,600
She turned off her phone.
We can't contact her.

239
00:42:25,320 --> 00:42:28,840
And the designer's gone too.
They're both gone.

240
00:42:30,120 --> 00:42:32,840
Taiga's working on a design for me.

241
00:42:33,800 --> 00:42:36,560
If believing that
makes you feel better, then sure.

242
00:42:41,440 --> 00:42:42,560
Can you contact her yet?

243
00:42:43,640 --> 00:42:44,840
She turned off her phone.

244
00:42:44,920 --> 00:42:46,440
Turned off her phone?

245
00:42:47,560 --> 00:42:48,440
What about her home?

246
00:42:49,680 --> 00:42:52,120
At the address she gave us, her apartment,

247
00:42:52,720 --> 00:42:53,840
I got no response.

248
00:42:53,920 --> 00:42:55,040
And her parents' home?

249
00:42:56,120 --> 00:42:57,520
Also no response.

250
00:42:57,600 --> 00:43:00,480
Both the designer
and the bodyguard are gone.

251
00:43:00,560 --> 00:43:04,320
I bet they've been boning
so many times they lost count.

252
00:43:10,360 --> 00:43:12,400
You can't go to work yet.

253
00:43:15,240 --> 00:43:16,640
I don't want to bother you.

254
00:43:20,840 --> 00:43:23,440
This house is large enough
that you can avoid me all day.

255
00:43:25,480 --> 00:43:29,280
I've arranged for a doctor.
He'll check on your wound every day.

256
00:43:31,640 --> 00:43:32,720
Thank you.

257
00:43:52,240 --> 00:43:55,000
Get well first. Don't come in to work yet.

258
00:43:55,840 --> 00:43:57,800
I'll count it as if
you're still working for me.

259
00:43:57,880 --> 00:44:02,040
If anything related to Taiga comes up,
you report it to me only.

260
00:44:02,880 --> 00:44:04,000
Yes, sir.

261
00:44:11,600 --> 00:44:13,480
{\an8}Greeting me with a bullet, huh, Khanin?

262
00:44:13,560 --> 00:44:16,320
{\an8}It's the best way to greet an old boss.

263
00:44:16,400 --> 00:44:17,840
{\an8}It's about damn time

264
00:44:17,920 --> 00:44:19,800
{\an8}you took responsibility
for everything, Punlop.

265
00:44:19,880 --> 00:44:21,280
{\an8}Pok, Prab, Pun.

266
00:44:21,880 --> 00:44:23,080
{\an8}You know this family?

267
00:44:23,160 --> 00:44:24,400
{\an8}This kid is me.

268
00:44:24,480 --> 00:44:26,640
{\an8}I'm the only son who survived.

269
00:44:26,720 --> 00:44:29,640
{\an8}If we get it wrong two more times,
we're locked out for good.

270
00:44:30,440 --> 00:44:32,120
{\an8}Maybe the answer lies in there.

271
00:45:04,920 --> 00:45:09,080
